Class AbstractAccessRuleProxy

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractLazyLoadingDtoProxy
      • org.phoenixbioinformatics.api.db.api.AbstractAccessRuleProxy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto, com.poesys.db.dto.IObserver, com.poesys.db.dto.ISubject, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto>, IAccessRule
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AccessRuleProxy

    public abstract class AbstractAccessRuleProxy
extends com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractLazyLoadingDtoProxy
implements IAccessRule

    A data-access layer data-transfer object (DTO) lazy-loading proxy for the AccessRule. This class is an abstract class that contains AndroMDA generated code; change nothing in this class. Instead, override any methods in the concrete subclass generated in the same package. AndroMDA will overwrite this class each time you run it but will never overwrite the concrete subclass.

    A rule that links a set of URIs to a specific access type for a specific partner

    Author:
    Poesys/DB Cartridge
